  <title>GLib.base64_encode</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function base64_encode(data: ByteArray): String {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_base64_encode()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Encode a sequence of binary data into its Base-64 stringified
representation.</p>
  <p>Since 2.12</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>data</code></title>
  <p>the binary data to encode</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a newly allocated, zero-terminated Base-64
              encoded string representing <code>data</code>. The returned string must
              be freed with <link xref="GLib.free"/>.</p>
</item>
</terms>

